# Band 8 Sample Answer

## Introduction

The pie chart illustrates the destinations of Anthropology graduates from one university after completing their undergraduate studies, while the table compares the salaries earned by anthropologists working in three different sectors after five years of employment.

**翻译：**
该饼图展示了某大学人类学毕业生在完成本科学业后的去向，而表格则比较了这些人类学毕业生在工作五年后于三个不同领域中的薪资情况。

---

## Overview

Overall, the majority of Anthropology graduates entered full-time employment after graduation, whereas only a relatively small proportion combined part-time work with postgraduate study. In terms of salaries, anthropologists working in the government sector and as freelance consultants tended to earn higher incomes than those employed by private companies.

**翻译：**
总体来看，大多数人类学毕业生在毕业后选择了全职工作，而只有较小比例的人选择一边兼职一边继续深造。就薪资而言，在政府部门和担任自由顾问的人类学家通常比在私营公司工作的人收入更高。

---

## Body Paragraph 1

According to the pie chart, 52% of graduates secured full-time jobs, making it the most common destination. Part-time employment accounted for 15%, while 12% of graduates were unemployed. In addition, 8% pursued full-time postgraduate study, and the same proportion fell into the “not known” category. By contrast, only 5% combined part-time work with postgraduate education, representing the smallest group.

**翻译：**
根据饼图，52%的毕业生获得了全职工作，这是最主要的去向。选择兼职工作的占15%，而12%的毕业生处于失业状态。此外，8%的学生继续进行全日制研究生学习，同样比例的人去向未知。相比之下，仅有5%的毕业生一边兼职一边继续深造，是占比最小的群体。

---

## Body Paragraph 2

Turning to the salary table, the government sector recorded the highest proportion of employees earning more than $100,000, at 50%. Freelance consultants also performed well, with 40% earning between $75,000 and $99,999 and another 40% receiving salaries above $100,000. Meanwhile, anthropologists employed by private companies were more concentrated in the middle-income range, as 35% earned between $50,000 and $74,999. Only 10% of private-sector employees earned below $50,000, compared with 5% in both the government sector and freelance consulting.

**翻译：**
再来看薪资表，政府部门中收入超过10万美元的员工比例最高，达到50%。自由顾问的收入情况也十分可观，其中40%的收入位于7.5万至9.9万美元之间，另有40%的收入超过10万美元。与此同时，在私营公司工作的人类学家更多集中于中等收入区间，因为有35%的人的收入在5万至7.4万美元之间。只有10%的私营企业员工收入低于5万美元，而政府部门和自由顾问这一比例均仅为5%。

